This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with improving models for detecting players in sports games using image cues. The use of a latent SVM learning algorithm and deformable part models also suggests a machine learning (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of Adaboost algorithm, which is a popular machine learning algorithm, further supporting the likelihood of it belonging to the machine learning sub-category. The paper's focus on self-learning and label acquisition also suggests a potential fit for the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of unlabelled data and discovering additional labels suggests a potential fit for the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
